[2/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q4  Primary 5  (13.4s)
============================================================
STEM: Either Daisy or her cousins ___ prepared the cake for the party this weekend.
  (1) did
  (2) will
  (3) has
  (4) have
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (682 chars):
The rule being tested is **subject-verb agreement** for the conjunction **"either... or"**, where the verb must agree with the subject closest to it.

Since the closest subject is the plural noun **"cousins"**, we must use the plural helping verb **"have"** to match it. This correctly forms the **present perfect tense** "**have prepared**".

**(1) did**: This is a **wrong verb form** error because **"did"** must be followed by a base verb, not "prepared".
**(2) will**: This is also a **wrong verb form** error because **"will"** requires a base verb.
**(3) has**: This is a **mismatched subject** error because **"has"** is singular and does not match the plural **"cousins"**.

