[4/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q6  Primary 5  (10.0s)
============================================================
STEM: Mary, ___ friend owns a restaurant, works as a reporter.
  (1) who
  (2) which
  (3) whom
  (4) whose
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (603 chars):
This question tests your understanding of **relative pronouns** to show possession. We use **whose** to show that the "friend" belongs to Mary. It correctly links Mary to her friend, meaning "Mary's friend owns a restaurant", making **(4)** the right choice!

Here is why the other options are incorrect:
**(1)** fails because **who** is a subject pronoun used for a person doing an action, not for ownership.
**(2)** fails because **which** is used for animals or things, not people.
**(3)** fails because **whom** is an object pronoun used when a person receives an action, not for showing possession.

