[5/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q8  Primary 5  (11.0s)
============================================================
STEM: Ravi looked ___ his older brother for support when he asked their mother if they could keep a pet.
  (1) to
  (2) into
  (3) over
  (4) after
ANSWER: 1

ELABORATION (675 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **phrasal verbs**, which combine a **verb** with a **preposition** to create a completely new meaning.

Option **(1)** is correct because "looked to" means to rely on someone for help or advice. Ravi is hoping his brother will help him convince their mother!

Option **(2)** is incorrect because "looked into" means to investigate a problem, which gives the wrong meaning here.
Option **(3)** is incorrect because "looked over" means to quickly examine or read something, which does not fit the context.
Option **(4)** is incorrect because "looked after" means to take care of someone or something, which makes no sense in this sentence.

