[6/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q9  Primary 5  (19.5s)
============================================================
STEM: Not only _____     Amir     _____ his dinner early, but he also washed the dishes.
  (1) did ... finish
  (2) is ... finishing
  (3) does ... finish
  (4) was ... finishing
ANSWER: 1

ELABORATION (579 chars):
The rule being tested is **negative inversion** and **tense consistency**.

When a sentence starts with "Not only", we swap the helping verb and subject. Since the second action "washed" is in the **simple past tense**, we must match it using "did" and the **base verb** "finish", making **(1)** correct.

**(2)** fails because it uses the **present continuous tense**, clashing with "washed".
**(3)** fails because it uses the **simple present tense**.
**(4)** fails because it uses the **past continuous tense**, but finishing dinner was a completed action, not an ongoing one.

