[7/10] P5 English EOY Nanyang 2025 — Q10  Primary 5  (16.0s)
============================================================
STEM: All the furniture ___ moved to the store room last Friday to prepare for the repainting next week.
  (1) has
  (2) was
  (3) have
  (4) were
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (641 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** with uncountable nouns and the **simple past tense**.

The word "furniture" is an **uncountable noun**, which means we must treat it as singular and use a **singular verb**. Since the moving happened "last Friday", we need the **past tense**, making **(2)** "was" the correct choice!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** fails because "has" forms the **present perfect tense** and is active voice, not the passive past tense.
**(3)** fails because "have" is a **plural verb** and the wrong tense.
**(4)** fails because "were" is a **plural verb**, but "furniture" needs a singular verb.

