[8/10] P5 English EOY Raffles 2025 — Q1  Primary 5  (11.4s)
============================================================
STEM: The price of rice ___ gone up significantly. We must not waste any grain of rice.
  (1) is
  (2) are
  (3) has
  (4) have
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (661 chars):
This question tests **Subject-Verb Agreement** and the **Present Perfect Tense**.

The true subject of the sentence is the **singular noun** "price" (not "rice"), so we need a **singular verb**. We use the **singular verb** "**has**" with the past participle "gone" to form the **Present Perfect Tense**, showing an action that affects the present.

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1) is**: This forms an incorrect grammatical structure ("is gone up" instead of "has gone up").
**(2) are**: This is a **plural verb** and forms an incorrect grammatical structure.
**(4) have**: This is a **plural verb**, which mismatches our **singular subject** "price".

